  "text": "The implementation follows Firefox's established XPCOM component patterns found in the mozilla-firefox/firefox repository. The header file uses NS_DECL_ISUPPORTS macro (xpcom/base/nsISupportsImpl.h) to declare reference counting methods (QueryInterface, AddRef, Release) and NS_DECL_NSIOBSERVERSERVICE macro to declare the observer service interface. The implementation file uses NS_IMPL_ISUPPORTS (xpcom/base/nsISupportsImpl.h) which expands to NS_IMPL_ADDREF, NS_IMPL_RELEASE, and NS_IMPL_QUERY_INTERFACE to implement the reference counting pattern. The Create factory method follows the pattern shown in nsObserverService.cpp, taking REFNSIID and void** parameters and using QueryInterface for polymorphic type conversion. The NS_GENERIC_FACTORY_CONSTRUCTOR macro (xpcom/components/ModuleUtils.h) provides the factory constructor wrapper that instantiates the component and calls QueryInterface. Component registration uses the components.conf format (toolkit/components/places/components.conf, xpcom/ds/components.conf) with legacy_constructor pointing to the Create method. The pattern ensures proper reference counting, interface negotiation, and component lifecycle management consistent with Firefox's XPCOM component architecture."
}

